column10:
started with y0, then went with yakuza kiwami, now im here. Gotta admit, kiwami 2 is a mixed baggage.

Cons:
- the fighting changed, due to the nature of the engine, every npc goes flying after a damn jump charged punch - hilarious though
- grabbing is OP and in a lot of situations; you can kill certain bosses with punch while grabbed; - easy to abuse 
- weapons are useful now, like too useful; they deal quite a lot of DMG and at the same time you find them everywhere. - shindo fell by spamming heavy attack with a katana for 20 times
- overall the engine upgrade makes the fighting more fluid to a point you can't just get used to it; feels like you bought a new car yet still crave your old daily driver;
- the plot is intricate yet forgettable; too many quickly introduced only to get discarded characters; this makes you not get attached to any; to add salt to injury you get thrown into plenty plot changes or updates over time in a quick succession;
- weird and poorly done facial expressions and at times lipsync - best example is the cabaret club intro mission;
- forgettable karaoke songs, kiwami 1 had the same issue;
- boss battles are too forgiving, so far only ryujin proved a challenge; 
- did i mention how exploitable are certain aspects to severely decrease the difficulty (playin on hard btw) ? looking at you, weapons with  over 20 charges scattered everywhere;
 - so far, no goromi :(
 - no intro theme song - wasted opportunity to get a guitar riff stuck in my head for a few days/weeks
 - for playing just the first cabaret club mission, feels like a downgrade from y0, but im not that harsh on it since y2 did not have cabaret club; 
 - they removed the fighting styles and now you have just brawler - wtf... no wonder im spamming triangle with weapons
 - you get a quick time event when the boss is at half of the last bar of HP, and instantly kill him - at this point i worked my ass off to scrape 5 bars, why bother at the end? - i didnt like the KIWAMI quick time event due to it appearing 3-7 times during a fight but the timing made sense;

pros:
- kiryu's sidekick is a nicely written character;
- the visuals are stunning; kamurocho never looked this good;
- you can enter stores without a loading screen :O
- the leveling up and spending the points in abilities system always gets changed and i appreciate that, the devs get to experiment; - fuck y0's system of having to be a trillionaire to have all the moves unlocked;
 - majima is still present
 - you get new minigames
 - more taxi locations
 - they kept certain sfx and songs from y0 in the cabaret club - i wanna be you giiirl
 - date-san is back
 - no more kiwami quick time event
- environment weapons, such as bicycles are less durable, forcing you to rely less on them;
 - fighting off npcs on the street is slightly more entertaining now, due to the goofiness of the engine with its ragdoll physics;


as of chapter 10, i do recommend the game but is WAY worse that the other two i've played - feels like a waste of time but compared to the state of gaming nowadays, it gets a pass;

