It's Yakuza 2 remade with advanced graphics (duh!), new minigames and a short Majima saga. The combat is quite realistic, but for some it may not be as eclectic and optional as in Yakuza 0 and Kiwami 1. On the other hand, using weapons is more practical. It's one of my favourites.

>I haven't finished the game yet, as i'm writing this i just did the Majima Construction quest.<

Everything in this game is as good as 0 and Kiwami or improved, except for one: Combat.

It's terrible.

- There's no flow of combat. A mere block can stop your combo;
Actually the inexistent flow of combat shows on every encounter you have and it's even worse on bosses.
- You get ragdolled in a silly manner if you get knocked down, it breaks immersion even;
- The lock on is terrible;
For you at least, on the enemies it's so great that if you hit the from behind the automatically turn towards you mid combo and guess what... They block, or dodge, or parry, or poise like if they're wearing a full Havel set and break your flow of combat.
- Remember styles from 0 and Kiwami? Yes they're gone, you're stuck with Dragon of Dojima style. And a gimped one that you must level and yada yada;
- Have i mentioned that the flow of combat of this game is broken all the time and at times you'll fight bosses by hitting one or two light punches or spamming charged atacks? All those things that you learned from the previous titles are thrown out of the window.

I hope it get's better.
